User Journey Map: College Student Diet Planning

STAGE 1: Waking Up
Action: Student wakes up late
Thought: "No time for breakfast"
Emotion: Rushed, Stressed
Touchpoint: Phone alarm, Hostel room

STAGE 2: Going to College
Action: Skips breakfast, drinks tea/coffee
Thought: "I will eat in canteen later"
Emotion: Hungry, Tired
Touchpoint: Canteen

STAGE 3: Afternoon Lunch
Action: Eats whatever is available in mess
Thought: "Don't know calories in this food"
Emotion: Confused
Touchpoint: Mess, Food

STAGE 4: Evening Snacks
Action: Orders junk food online
Thought: "Feeling low energy, need something tasty"
Emotion: Guilty but craving
Touchpoint: Food delivery app

STAGE 5: Night Time
Action: Searches for diet plans on Google
Thought: "I should eat healthy from tomorrow"
Emotion: Motivated but overwhelmed
Touchpoint: Google, YouTube

PAIN POINTS:
1. No clear nutrition info
2. No personalized suggestions
3. Too much junk food consumption

OPPORTUNITY:
Create a Tableau dashboard that analyzes food data and gives easy diet suggestions to students
